        <locationX>1331</locationX>
        <locationY>252</locationY>
        <defaultConnectorLabel>&lt; 3 Days Ago</defaultConnectorLabel>
        <rules>
            <name>More_Than_3_Days_Ago</name>
            <conditionLogic>and</conditionLogic>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>forB_SchoolCreatedLessThreeDays</leftValueReference>
                <operator>EqualTo</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <booleanValue>true</booleanValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <connector>
                <targetReference>Owner_Email_Provided</targetReference>
            </connector>
            <label>&gt; 3 Days Ago</label>
        </rules>
    </decisions>
    <description>Matches unlinked premium school objects to existing or new accounts
10/09/23 - Update flow to only run on school object records created more than three days ago. (Sprint 18)
03/14/24 - PE - Updated entry criteria to only run on schools where Number of Sites = 1
07/17/24 - PE - Updated entry criteria to not pull schools without name as this causes errors when creating accounts. 
05/19/25 - AC - Update create new account node removing reference to Account Status

Diagram: https://drive.google.com/file/d/12vtMO5Tx16CzpZ6zRlZGCAttfaUPLgWV/view?usp=sharing</description>
    <environments>Default</environments>
    <formulas>
        <description>This formula checks if a record was created more than three days ago, returning true if so, and false otherwise.</description>
        <name>forB_SchoolCreatedLessThreeDays</name>
        <dataType>Boolean</dataType>
        <expression>DATEVALUE({!$Record.CreatedDate}) &lt; TODAY() - 3</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <description>When the flow identifies a parent account for the new account record being created, it sets the Parent Account field with that account ID. If no parent account is found, the Parent Account field remains unassigned.</description>
        <name>forT_AssignParentAccount</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>IF(
{!$Record.Number_of_Sites__c} = 2
&amp;&amp;
NOT(ISNULL({!Get_Parent_Account.Id})),
{!Get_Parent_Account.Id},
IF(
{!$Record.Number_of_Sites__c} &gt; 2
&amp;&amp;
NOT(ISNULL({!Look_For_a_Parent_Account.ParentId})) ,
{!Look_For_a_Parent_Account.ParentId},
&quot;&quot;
)
)</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <description>Returns &apos;Single-Site&apos; if the &apos;Number of Sites&apos; on the school object field is set to 1. Otherwise, if the value is greater than 1, returns &apos;Multi-Site Child&apos;.</description>
        <name>forT_CustomerType</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>If(
{!$Record.Number_of_Sites__c} &lt;= 1, &quot;Single-Site&quot;,
&quot;Multi-Site Child&quot;
)</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <description>Evaluates if any lead was located in the &apos;Get Leads&apos; element and determines if the lead is linked to an organization. If so, it outputs the organization&apos;s ID; otherwise, it returns null.</description>
        <name>forT_LeadOrganization</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>IF(
AND(
NOT(ISNULL({!Get_Leads.Id})),
NOT(ISNULL({!Get_Leads.Organization__c}))
),
{!Get_Leads.Organization__c},
&quot;&quot;
)</expression>
    </formulas>
